## v1.3.0 (2026-04-14)

**Changed by:** ArchIdeas session — first accuracy review-and-fix pass on the 39-idea corpus (Phase C)
**Verification:** verified-local

### What changed
- Added Phase C: Accuracy Review-and-Fix Pass (in-place, marker-free) section covering when to use Phase C vs Phase B, the 7-priority fix order, two-wave structure (17+22), three citation manifest formats, fix discipline rules, LoRA case taxonomy, and SwiGLU ×3 factor
- Added Baseline C (K2 Family / LLM360) specs to Verified On table entry
- Added 5 new Failed Attempts rows: marker-free discipline (no `[corrected: ...]` markers), pre-existing `## Corrections applied:` not being banned content, 39-lead Phase C wave limit, H_q misuse in attention FLOPs formula, SwiGLU FLOPs = 3×d×d_ff not 2×d×d_ff
- Bumped version to 1.3.0

### Why
The ArchIdeas corpus completed its first accuracy review-and-fix pass (Phase C). This phase is distinct from Phase B (merge): it is an in-place surgical fix pass with no output files, no inline correction markers, and verdicts explicitly out of scope. The two-wave limit (17+22), three citation manifest formats, and SwiGLU/LoRA FLOPs corrections were all new learnings not captured in v1.2.0.

